## Part 3: What's Missing

| Gap | Risk | Status |
|-----|------|--------|
| No definition of what replaces `GateAction` enum | Lane C is unimplementable | ✅ **Resolved** (Replaced by `control_signals` strings) |
| No LLM mocking/recording strategy for replay | Lane B exit gate is unachievable | 🟡 Unresolved |
| No definition of "repeated-failure motif" | Lane E exit gate is unevaluable | 🟡 Unresolved |
| `simulate_operations()` heuristics not scoped into Lane C | Heuristic drift will persist in simulation path | ✅ **Resolved** (Heuristics scrubbed) |
| No API/interface contract for "learned graph control objects" | Refactor could sprawl without bounds | ✅ **Resolved** (Using `control_signals`) |
| No mention of the `GateType` duplication between `predicate.rs` and `types.rs` | Two parallel gate enums exist; refactor must reconcile them | ✅ **Resolved** (Enums deleted) |

